const content = `<h2>Solar & HVAC in Denver, Colorado</h2>
<p>Denver, Colorado presents an exceptional opportunity for solar energy adoption and efficient HVAC systems. With over 715,522 residents in Denver County, the city enjoys approximately 300 days of sunshine annually, making it one of the premier locations for solar panel installations in the United States. The city's high altitude of 5,280 feet and Cold-Dry climate create ideal conditions for solar panel efficiency, as photovoltaic systems perform better in cooler temperatures while still receiving abundant sunlight. Xcel Energy serves as the primary utility provider, offering electricity at rates of 12.5¬¢/kWh, which makes solar energy a financially attractive investment for homeowners looking to reduce their energy costs.</p>

<p>The Cold-Dry climate of Denver creates unique advantages for both solar and HVAC systems. The low humidity levels mean less strain on air conditioning systems during summer months, while the abundant sunshine provides excellent solar production potential year-round. With average home sizes of 1,920 square feet, Denver homeowners typically see substantial savings when combining efficient HVAC systems with solar panel installations. The city's commitment to renewable energy, coupled with Xcel Energy's net metering programs and various state incentives, makes Denver an ideal market for homeowners considering solar panel installations and HVAC upgrades.</p>

